mmunity and cultural aspects. Shared concerns over energy conservation, social protection and inclusion, and the roles and responsibilities of the public and private sectors form the basis of a proposed policy agenda for housing renewal across Europe. The concluding chapters draw conclusions from a pan-European perspective and consider the future prospects for renewing older housing. Academics, practitioners, policy-makers and students of housing, urban studies, planning, regeneration, environmental health and sustainability will all want to read this book.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aHousing policyzEurope. 0aPublic housingzEurope. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aBrown, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFijalkow, Yankel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedrichs, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGunay, Zeynep, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoramaz, T Kerem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLévy-Vroelant, Claire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Rolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOjamäe, Liis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOzuekren, A Sule, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPaadam, Katrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPareja-Eastaway, Montserrat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimó-Solsona, Montse, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrubelt, Wendelin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTosics, Iván, econtributor.4ctb4ht